                        <interp inst="t18400615-name-254" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>ELIZABETH PITTIS.</persName>
                  </hi>I live with my parents. On the 25th of May I was in St. James's Park, between St. James's and Buckingham Palace—the prisoner was near me on my left side, and then he was at my back—I told him not to push—he then came on my left side, and I felt his hand in my pocket—before I had time to speak, the policeman had him—I had two silver thimbles, a key, and some halfpence in my pocket.</p>
